history.content:
Prerequisite are not enforced in most ee/cs courses, so you won't be blocked from enrolling even if you don't have a prereq. For eecs 127, if you have strong linear algebra and math background then you should be fine without 16b.

--------------------------------------------------------

16B is a prerequisite for 127 and though some prerequisites aren't needed, I would say this is highly highly recommended. I would only take 127 without 16B if you got an A in math 54 and really mastered all the linear algebra concepts.
